a,b>0,r>1\implies \sqrt[r]{a+b}\leq\sqrt[r]{a}+\sqrt[r]{b}. 
a,b,r
a,b,r
0<\dfrac{1}{r}<1
 1\le \left(\frac{a}{a+b}\right)^{1/r}+\left(\frac{b}{a+b}\right)^{1/r}. 
 0<\frac{a}{a+b},\,\frac{b}{a+b}<1, 
 \left(\frac{a}{a+b}\right)^{1/r}>\frac{a}{a+b}\,\,\,\,\,\text{and}\,\,\,\,\, \left(\frac{b}{a+b}\right)^{1/r}>\frac{b}{a+b}, 
 \left(\frac{a}{a+b}\right)^{1/r}+\left(\frac{b}{a+b}\right)^{1/r}> \frac{a}{a+b}+\frac{b}{a+b}=1. 
(\sqrt[r]{a+b})^r \leq (\sqrt[r]{a}+\sqrt[r]{b})^r \implies a+b \leq (\sqrt[r]{a})^r + (\sqrt[r]{b})^r + positiveterms 
